  "text": "Chazelle et al. [CITATION_1] introduced a simplex range searching method that answers queries in O(n 1−1/d+ ) time by using O(n 1+ ) preprocessing time and O(n) space, for any arbitrary small positive constant . They also obtained a trade-off between storage and query time. They showed that one can build a data structure of size O(m) in time O(m 1+ ), where n ≤ m ≤ n d , so that the query can be",
